Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle, gradual curve. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium red-brown; mixed inclusions.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. For a parallel see V. Grace, BCH Suppl. XIII 559. no. 24; she interprets the second letter as omega, but on neither piece is there a spur to the left. From the same die as 2011,5003.473
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1612)
